
These instructions will guide you how to get a complete build environment
for showtime

Create a new directory with the name of your choice, then donwload and
extract packages for these projects into it:

freetype, http://www.freetype.org/

Now copy the buildenv* scripts to the new directory:

There are two script for building build envionments
buildenv.10.4-i386-ppc.sh:
gcc 4.0, 10.4 SDK, compiles for PPC and i386 

buildenv.10.6-i386-x86_64.sh:
latest gcc (4.2 on 10.6), 10.6 SDK, compiles for i386 and x86 64

buildenv.common.sh is helpt script used by both buildscripts

After you have copied the files you may want to change the
INSTALLDIR variable in the build scripts

When done run:
$ sh buildenv.10.4-i386-ppc.sh
Or
$ sh buildenv.10.6-i386-x86_64

Now you can compile showtime using

./configure --cc="gcc-4.0 -arch i386" --macosx-sdk=/Developer/SDKs/MacOSX10.4u.sdk --pkg-config-dir=$HOME/install-10.4-i386-ppc/lib/pkgconfig/
Or
./configure --cc="gcc -arch i386" --macosx-sdk=/Developer/SDKs/MacOSX10.6.sdk/ --pkg-config-dir=$HOME/install-10.6-i386-x86_64/lib/pkgconfig/

You can also compile for PPC or x86 64 using something like:

./configure --arch=powerpc --cc="gcc-4.0 -arch ppc" --macosx-sdk=/Developer/SDKs/MacOSX10.4u.sdk --pkg-config-dir=$HOME/install-10.4-i386-ppc/lib/pkgconfig/

